  "text": "Preparation and recording procedures. ORC s were dissociated enzymatically from the olfactory epithelium of the newt Cynops pyrrhogaster, as reported [CITATION_1] . Isolated cells were viewed on an Olympus upright microscope with differential interference contrast optics (40ϫ water-immersion objective). Membrane voltages and currents were recorded in the whole-cell configuration [CITATION_2] ) using a patch-clamp amplifier (Axopatch 200B; Axon Instruments, Foster C ity, CA) linked to a computer. Recording procedures were controlled by pC lamp software (Axon Instruments). Data were low-pass-filtered (fourpole Bessel type) with a cutoff frequency of 5 kHz and then digitized at 10 kHz by an analog-to-digital interface. All experiments were done at room temperature (23-25°C).",
